comments.body:
That is incorrect. The function is testing whether `node` is an _IdentifierName_ in ES. The _IdentifierName_ production is generally used for property names (i.e. `({ foo: 1 })` or `obj.foo`), where reserved words are not forbidden. A `QualifiedName` is a TS-only syntax, but is essentially similar to a property access expression when used as an expression. The name of a `QualifiedName` should always be considered an _IdentifierName_, even when it is not the child of a `TypeQuery` or `TypeReference`. The case this addresses is this:

```ts
export {};
import X = someNamespace.await;
```

Without this change, we would incorrectly error on `await` since the namespace import is at the top level of a module.

